- The integer array parameter `forts` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `forts` must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 1000.
- The integer array parameter `forts` can contain values of -1, 0, or 1.
- The integer result is the maximum number of enemy forts that can be captured by moving the army from one of your forts to an empty position.
- If it is impossible to move the army or there are no forts under your command, the integer result is 0.